{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"71954a9e-4997-4562-98fc-875b82e8a811","content":"Here's what I found:\n\n**`my_app/views.py:3`** — `datetime.now()` is called directly, making it hard to mock in tests.\n\n```\nnow = datetime.now()\n```\n\n### Recommendation\n\nInject the clock dependency via Django's `django.utils.timezone.now` instead, which is easier to patch:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()  # patchable via @mock.patch('django.utils.timezone.now')\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThis also gives you timezone-aware datetimes (important when `USE_TZ=True`). In tests you can simply:\n\n```python\n@mock.patch('django.utils.timezone.now', return_value=datetime(2026, 1, 1))\n```\n\nOnly **1 occurrence** found in this project. Want me to apply the fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9c7a595f-2d7d-4ba2-94aa-2e5a4e582cfd","outputTokens":228,"requestId":"3411:47F73:F2639D:11D5161:69F413A2"},"id":"78757733-6282-4b27-b986-71a2444cf6de","timestamp":"2026-05-01T02:44:56.818Z","parentId":"8b1b5f9e-4ae5-4ec7-871a-3d384ebb27e7"}
